ce\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003EScience\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E);\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n\n            \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003EDebug\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003ELog\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E(\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022str\u0022\u003E\u0022Scale \u0022\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E\u002B\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003EUIMasterController\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022typ\u0022\u003EInstance\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E.\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003EuiScale\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E);\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pln\u0022\u003E\n        \u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan class=\u0022pun\u0022\u003E}\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/pre\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLooking at the console, RnDComplexSpawn runs before I get the message [UIMasterController]:ShowUI, so that\u0027s why I tried checking for onShowUI, but that still runs after ComplexSpawn and before the UIMasterController message. If I try using RDController in either of them, I get a nullReferenceException.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: Actually, I can see researchCanvas() running with an instanced RDController, but only when I exit the R\u0026amp;D building. Perhaps I have to wait for something else?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can use ResearchAndDevelopment, but that only has operations for the actual science and experiments.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI can also reach UIMasterController, but can\u0027t see any way to use it to detect RDController.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222021-12-30T16:18:11Z\u0022 title=\u002212/30/2021 04:18  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 30, 2021\u003C/time\u003E by IC-Adel\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gotmachine","CreatedById":163039,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-31T00:33:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRDController.OnRDTreeSpawn is the callback you\u0027re looking for.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"IC-Adel","CreatedById":218337,"CreatedDateTime":"2021-12-31T15:21:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks, that worked.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt seems the size is controlled by RDController.Instance.gridArea.gridBackground.sizeDelta.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlthough I\u0027m having trouble with the zoom, as it snaps to the center of the older sized grid, I guess the gridArea.scrollRect needs to be resized, too, or maybe it has something to do with gridArea CalculateSnapBounds(), CenterOfGrid() or Snap().\u00A0 Setting the max and min zoom to 1 doesn\u0027t solve it, either, as the snap still gets called for any zoom input.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGuess I\u0027ll have to do some more digging.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}